It may also have been a helicopter that departed as a charter or tour from another City but flew over NYC airspace. Helicopter tours originating from outside NYC are not subject to the same City regulations as tours departing from heliports managed by NYCEDC. Any City regulation of these flights is pre-empted by federal law and subject only to the jurisdiction of the Federal Aviation Administration.
